Hadrian Residential Bootcamp is a 'non military' style bootcamp with a focus on both physical and mental fitness. We believe that in order to achieve results, people should look after both their physical and mental fitness and develop strategies to make lasting changes to live healthy lifestyles. Hadrian is about giving people the information and support to overcome obstacles they may face, in order to achieve their health and fitness goals. Hadrian is based on the Cumbria/Northumberland border, nestled in over 90 acres of beautiful private countryside and provides residential bootcamps from Monday to Friday. If you join us at Hadrian, you can expect to enjoy a full programme of activity to include physical activity sessions and daily workshops on nutrition, mental fitness and physical activity. The activities utilise the beautiful natural surroundings including spending time along the historic Hadrian's Wall. You will also receive tasty, nutritious and satisfying food which is prepared on site by our resident chef and at the end of each day take to your bed in 4 star cottage accommodation. Various forms of exercise will be used eg strength, resistance, cardiovascular, etc and you will be provided with workshops to fully explain the benefits of each. We provide daily coaching workshops as we believe that having a goal in mind strengthens the bootcamp experience by providing a focus for each individual. You will also receive daily nutritional workshops to ensure you feel fully equip to eat well once you return home. At Hadrian we offer spaces to individuals and groups and the cottages are set up to accommodate the group as necessary. We also offer corporate spaces on all of our bootcamps and we encourage businesses to invest in the health and fitness of their employees by securing a number of places. We can also offer bespoke bootcamps for individual businesses ranging from 2 - 5 nights. The maximum occupancy on any of our bootcamps is 17 people.
